# Railway Environment Variables Template
# Copy these variables to your Railway project's Variables tab

# ===================
# REQUIRED VARIABLES
# ===================

# OpenAI API Configuration (REQUIRED)
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Node.js Environment
NODE_ENV=production

# ===================
# OPTIONAL VARIABLES
# ===================

# Performance Optimization
NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=4096

# NPM Configuration
NPM_CONFIG_CACHE=/tmp/.npm

# ===================
# AUTO-CONFIGURED BY RAILWAY
# ===================

# Railway automatically sets these - DO NOT set manually:
# PORT=5000 (Railway dynamically assigns port)
# RAILWAY_ENVIRONMENT_NAME=production
# RAILWAY_PROJECT_NAME=your-project-name
# RAILWAY_SERVICE_NAME=your-service-name

# ===================
# DOMAIN CONFIGURATION
# ===================

# After domain setup, Railway automatically configures:
# RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN=translatorassistant.com
# RAILWAY_PRIVATE_DOMAIN=your-app-name.railway.app

# ===================
# INSTRUCTIONS
# ===================

# 1. Go to your Railway project dashboard
# 2. Click on "Variables" tab
# 3. Add each variable above (except the auto-configured ones)
# 4. For OPENAI_API_KEY, paste your actual API key
# 5. Save and redeploy if necessary

# ===================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ===================

# - Never commit your actual API key to git
# - Use Railway's Variables tab for all secrets
# - Keep your API key secure and rotate it regularly
# - Monitor your OpenAI usage to prevent unexpected costs